parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Main Air Brake Line Rubbing Against Retaining Bracket
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of the main air brake line due to rubbing against the retaining bracket can lead to air brake system failure, potentially causing accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: None reported
as this issue is related to wear and tear
but drivers may experience sudden loss of air brake pressure
reduced braking performance
or warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Failure to Receive Recall Parts from Blue Bird
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or failure to receive recall parts from Blue Bird can leave vehicles unrepaired, potentially leading to safety risks and continued operation with defective components.
symptoms: Vehicle owners experience prolonged wait times for recall parts
failure to receive parts
and lack of communication from Blue Bird regarding the status of parts delivery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incomplete or inadequate repair of vehicles under Recall 96V126.001 can lead to continued safety risks, including potential accidents or injuries, due to the presence of defective components.
symptoms: Vehicle owners report that their vehicles have not been properly repaired
or that the repairs did not address the underlying safety issues
despite the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Lock-Up due to Horn Ring Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn ring can cause the steering column to lock up, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or locks up
the horn ring is stuck or peeling
the steering column feels rough or binding
the vehicle is hard to steer or maneuver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle cable can cause the engine to stall or hesitate, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The throttle cable breaks
the engine stalls or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the accelerator pedal feels loose or unresponsive
the vehicle is difficult to control.
